{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "SHELF/vellum_balloon", "parent": "vellum"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Vellum Balloon"], "extent": [45, 64]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Configures vellum balloon from geometry and adds to current vellum simulation."], "extent": [64, 151]}, {"type": "video_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "video", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [151, 159], "body": [], "container": true, "attrs": {"src": "/videos/vellumballoon.mp4"}}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [196, 211], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This tool lets you pick a piece of geometry and configure it as vellum balloon.  It will then be added to the active simulation and merged with any other existing vellum objects."], "extent": [211, 392]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["A balloon consists of two types of constraints.  A stretchable cloth constraint is built for the outer surface.   A pressure constraint is added to keep the cloth from collapsing.  The pressure constraint uniformly pushes the cloth outwards to maintain a global volume, so squeezing one area will bulge distant areas."], "extent": [392, 711]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is more expensive than a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/vellumsoftbody", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Strut Softbody"], "fullpath": "/shelf/vellumsoftbody"}, " since instead of creating struts between opposite interior points, it computes the volume of the entire model and inflates or shrinks the model to keep the same volume. The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/vellumsoftbody", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Strut Softbody"], "fullpath": "/shelf/vellumsoftbody"}, " is a better choice for soft bodies as it is faster to solve."], "extent": [711, 1068]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1068, 1074], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The topology of your object could affect how pressure is applied. You may have to simplify the topology by using PolyReduce or increase the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Stiffness"]}, " parameter in the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pressure_constraints"]}, " node to properly inflate your object."], "extent": [1074, 1311]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "includeme", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Using Vellum Balloon"], "extent": [1311, 1350], "body": [{"type": "ord_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Select the geometry object to configure as vellum balloon."], "extent": [1350, 1421]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "ord", "indent": 4, "text": ["Click the ", {"scheme": "Icon", "value": "SHELF/vellum_balloon", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/shelf/SHELF/vellum_balloon"}, {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum Balloon"]}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum"]}, " tab."], "extent": [1421, 1512]}], "container": true}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 4, "role": "item", "extent": [1512, 1522], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["There is a ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/clothbodycollider", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Collider"], "fullpath": "/shelf/clothbodycollider"}, " tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Vellum"]}, " shelf that you can use for objects that will be colliding with your balloon. It is essentially the same as the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/deformingobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Deforming Object"], "fullpath": "/shelf/deformingobject"}, " shelf tool on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Collisions"]}, " tab, as they are both designed for deforming objects. However the ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/shelf/clothbodycollider", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface Collider"], "fullpath": "/shelf/clothbodycollider"}, " does not try to generate a VDB collision object, which is less expensive."], "extent": [1522, 1983]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For specific parameter information, see the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Constraints"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints"}, " and ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Solver"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/vellumsolver"}, " help."], "extent": [1983, 2124]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Working with Vellum Balloon"], "extent": [2124, 2158], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["By default the Stretch ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Stiffness"]}, " is very low, since balloons have to be able to stretch. "], "extent": [2158, 2254]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["There is an ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Output Group"]}, " parameter on the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["pressure_constraints"]}, " ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Constraints"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vellumconstraints"}, " node which adds the generated stretch constraints to this primitive group. This is useful so you can edit them later with a ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/vellumconstraintproperty", "type": "link", "text": ["Vellum Constraint Property DOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/vellumconstraintproperty"}, ". For example, you can output the pressure constraints and animate them using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Rest Length Scale"]}, " parameter."], "extent": [2254, 2676]}]}], "title": ["Vellum Balloon"], "summary": ["Configures vellum balloon from geometry and adds to current vellum simulation."]}